snippet.textDisplay:
Ap sabko sharam ani chahye waqay Pakistaniyo iss country ke har cheez ko tabah kernay me hum logo ka khud ka haath he. Coke Studio country ka asset he or uspe aisay bhoonk bhoonk ker tum isko bhe destroy ker doo. 
Kya tum log ye jante ho ke Rohail Season 6 ke badd kyun chorh ke gaya just because of all hate speech from media, society and jahil awaam jo ke international talent ko season 6 me anay ke wajah se galiyan nikal rahe the.
Har season me criticism hota ha iss bar to hadd he ker de he tum logo ne Samaa, Dawn, 92News, or dosray media channels takk tumhari Sayonee pe kee hui hate speech ko twitter pe headline bana ke bethe hue hein. 
Ager tum logo ke dil me itni nafrat bhari hui he to kahin or ja ke nikalo tum logo ke bakwas se lagta ha ke Coke Studio Season 10 ke baad ya to producers chorh denge ya show band ho jayega. 

Sayonee Ali Azmat ke pehchan or signature he ismay koi shak nai ha par itne bhe bakwaas na kero ke Show he band ho jaye. Mujh jaisay or bhe loog hein jinko ye rendition pasand aye he number of likes define ker rahe hein ke kitnay logo ne pasand kiya ha. Par apnay alfaazo pe qabooo rakho ye na ho ke kuch bathroom singers ke bakwas ke wajah se Coke Studio he bandd ho jaye.

Manjanib: Coke Studio Lover From Pakistan

snippet.textDisplay:
This song lacks the pain and truth of raw emotion compared to the previous version. It's like a castrated version of the original song but decorated with beautiful ornaments and clothing. The word 'Sayonee' in my mind always brings image of that lost child who looks around for his place in this chaotic world. There is no way to 'unhear' that one and then listen to this one. But if I heard this as the first version, honestly, it would never be as appealing or remarkable. I mean I was like 9 years old and this is the only song during that age that I can imagine so vividly. 
However, two pieces of art can never be compared without being subjective, so I am at peace with the fact that not everyone will agree with me. Let's how many people will feel the urge to come back to this tomorrow and the day after. I'm craving now to jump to the original version and will do as soon as I finish typing. Peace.
